  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, which warrants a penalty to deter future misconduct and reflect the gravity of white-collar crime. However, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration. The defendant has no prior criminal record, demonstrating that this is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of behavior. Additionally, the defendant has shown remorse and taken responsibility by partially repaying the stolen funds. Balancing the breach of duty with these mitigating circumstances, a brief period of incarceration is appropriate, followed by supervised release during which the defendant must pay full restitution.",
